es, and how we work. The Team Doist\u2019s Design team crafts engaging experiences to make people\u2019s lives more productive. Whether brainstorming marketing pages or functional interfaces, Design is always a core priority for Doist. We are now looking for a talented Product Designer to join our international team of Product Designers, Marketing Designers and Illustrators. Your Role As a Product Designer at Doist, you\u2019ll have an opportunity to collaborate not only with the other designers in the team but also with members of the development, marketing, and support teams. We always work together to create engaging, intuitive, easy to use, and delightful applications and experiences that promote balance in our users\u2019 lives. And because at Doist, we aim to create the best cross-platform apps, you will always be working on cross-platform solutions for both our products\u2014Todoist and Twist. About you To thrive as a Product Designer at Doist you are: Experienced with 3+ years in product design roles. Skilled and experienced in user experience and interface design, with a portfolio that demonstrates your skills. Experienced and comfortable working across different platforms Android, iOS, macOS and Web. And you know in depth the Google Material Design and Apple Human Interface Guidelines. Experienced with accessibility, animations, and user flows. Able to form, prototype, and clearly communicate your ideas and decisions. Experience using at least one of the following design tools\u2013Sketch, Figma, or Adobe XD. A user advocate. Able to work well on cross-functional and iterative teams. Responsible, self-motivated, and comfortable taking the initiative. Attentive to the finer details and love what you do. Fluent in written and spoken English. Comfortable communicating with a multicultural team with diverse communication styles, in multiple time zones. Bonus: Strong animation and video editing skills. Experience creating and maintaining design libraries. Experience running user testing sessions. Icon and illustration work. Knowledge of coding technologies and GIT. Requirements A complete application includes: A resume or manually entered experience (you can choose your preference). Thoughtful, thorough responses to all the application questions. No cover letter needed! Applications will be accepted until June 30th (or as long as the role is listed at doist.com/jobs). Invitations to the hiring process will be set out during the first week of July. The process will be as follows: Interview with Ana F., our Head of Design. We\u2019ll ask you to complete a test task. Interview with Alex M., a member of our Design team. Interview with Amir S., our Founder & CEO. Benefits Our perks and benefits are designed to provide the freedom and support you need to grow personally and professionally. Here\u2019s what that looks like: The basics Work from anywhere in the world. We never place restrictions on locations. Design your own schedule. Work no more than 40 hours/week. Competitive pay. Our formula-based salary calculation provides a highly competitive rate based on your skills and location. Expand your professional skills Pursue personal projects. All Doisters get one month per year to spend on a work-related project they\u2019re passionate about. Attend conferences. You\u2019ll have a recurring budget to spend on attending conferences that grow your professional knowledge, skills, and network. Company retreats. Our annual company-wide retreats are unforgettable. Craft your ideal work environment Cozy up at a coworking space. Find a coworking space that\u2019s right for you and Doist will cover the expense. Apps and services budget. You\u2019ll have a monthly budget to spend on services that help you do your job. Hardware budget. You\u2019ll have access to a recurring budget to spend on work-related equipment. Focus on your well-being Generous time off. Doisters get 8 weeks (40 days) of PTO/year to use as they wish on vacations and national holidays. Parental leave. New parents receive 5 weeks of paid parental leave in addition to 13 weeks of paid pregnancy-related medical leave. Invest in your health and wellness. You\u2019ll have a monthly budget to spend on things like gym membership, healthy snacks, massages, health insurance, etc. \u2014 All information collected through this application is stored in Workable, Doist\u2019s Applicant Tracking System, where it will be used for recruitment purposes only. For more information on how we handle candidate data at Doist, we invite you to review our recruitment privacy notice. For questions, please contact us at andrew.g@doist.com. If this job interests you but you aren\u2019t certain if you meet all of the\u00c2\u00a0requirements, apply anyway! More Jobs Website Twitter Or view all jobs: Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs & learn about: remote work Related Jobs Senior Product Designer TaxJar TaxJar makes sales tax filing easier for online sellers and merchants. See local jurisdictional tax reports, get payment reminders, and more! Anywhere Full Time Posted 5 days ago Senior Product Designer \u2013 Contract SmartContract Smart Contracts are self-executing contractual states, stored on the blockchain, which nobody controls and therefore everyone can trust. Anywhere Full Time Posted 2 weeks ago Senior Product Designer Komoot Change The Way People Explore Anywhere Full Time Posted 4 weeks ago MAIN Podcast Community Post a job Remote Work Virtual Wedding Instagram Twitter Login REMOTE JOBS Developer jobs Marketing jobs Product jobs Design jobs Sales jobs Support jobs JOBS IN YOUR CITY Los Angeles jobs New York City jobs San Francisco jobs Chicago jobs Seattle jobs Austin jobs London jobs Paris jobs Berlin jobs POST YOUR JOBS Post a job We\u2019ve helped the world\u2019s top companies hire a talented, diverse pool of job candidates \u2013 view our success stories here. Terms & Privacy Policy & hello@remotewo